Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.87,0:00:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.02,0:00:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.56,0:00:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.70,0:00:10.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your tea is overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.07,0:00:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that brat with the glasses caught a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.80,0:00:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the deciding moment that determines your future...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.62,0:00:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot lie to yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.04,0:00:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An awkward atmosphere lingers around Ran\Nand Shinichi after the long-coming reunion!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.83,0:00:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.46,0:00:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.64,0:02:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's waiting for us in London as soon as we arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.73,0:02:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was a coded message indicative of a massive murder manifesto.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.82,0:02:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to obtain some advice to solve the\Ncode, Ran called Shinichi's phone, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.12,0:02:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the call, I figured out that the first line of the cipher\Nwas about London's famous clock tower Big Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.21,0:02:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I inadvertently used Shinichi's voice to inform Ran about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.34,0:02:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was therefore chased by Ran who was\Nsure that Shinichi was in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.63,0:02:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having no choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.69,0:03:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was shortly after Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s phone call\Nlast night that he began trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.36,0:03:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must've been because he was running all\Naround London sweating up a storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.32,0:03:11.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that sweat got chilled by the night wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.12,0:03:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.37,0:03:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we're supposed to go back to Japan tomorrow night!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.75,0:03:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.75,0:03:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took some medicine and his fever went down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he should be fine after a day's rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.46,0:03:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.84,0:03:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't need to worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.34,0:03:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} and Uncle Kogorou, you guys go solve that code!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.59,0:03:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think those seven lines of code probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.35,0:03:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Refer to various buildings or places, so there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.14,0:03:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.11,0:03:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} said so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.36,0:03:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi did?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.86,0:03:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Said in front of Big Ben...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.41,0:03:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the "loud sound of a rolling bell"\Nin the first line was Big Ben's chime!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.12,0:03:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In front of Big Ben!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.62,0:04:02.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that detective brat came to London!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.92,0:04:04.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.09,0:04:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that, didn't you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.59,0:04:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I had known, why would I have made a souvenir list!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.01,0:04:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to take care of Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.18,0:04:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, much appreciated if I\Ncould ask you two to decipher the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.44,0:04:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We somehow managed to fool them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.69,0:04:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to think you'd use up the antidote for the return trip...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no choice, did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.82,0:04:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I hadn't taken it, it would've been revealed that Edogawa\NConan was the infantilized form of Kudou Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.21,0:04:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about your return trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.21,0:04:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no more medicine, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.58,0:04:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's not like I can ask Haibara to bring more to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.84,0:04:51.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll think of something while I'm cooped up in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.34,0:04:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not going to go out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.05,0:04:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to meet up with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}\Nand her father to solve that code?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.68,0:04:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.27,0:05:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know when my body's going to revert\Nback to being Conan, so how could I go out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.23,0:05:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.56,0:05:09.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think I can face her...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.07,0:05:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, take a look at this morning's newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.99,0:05:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Based on the fingerprints that were on\Nthe paper the code was written on...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.66,0:05:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've narrowed it down to one suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.54,0:05:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is Hades Sahara.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A serial murderer who's currently on the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.13,0:05:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, we need to research this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.13,0:05:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if they've already confirmed the\Nculprit, they'll arrest him soon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.51,0:05:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.01,0:05:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy left his fingerprints on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.43,0:05:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means he's doing this knowing full well that he'll be arrested!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.02,0:05:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having been told that the "loud sound of a rolling bell" is Big Ben...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.19,0:05:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd think that does make sense, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.65,0:05:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like there are buildings shaped like\Nan egg or pickles scattering around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.99,0:05:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.32,0:05:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.82,0:06:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there an egg-shaped building here in London?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.37,0:06:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah yes, there's a City Hall near the Tower Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.75,0:06:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would've thought there'd really be a building shaped like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.59,0:06:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.68,0:06:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The third line...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.80,0:06:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"My morsel is a boiled egg that's gone\Nas cold as a corpse" refers to...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.43,0:06:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This City Hall, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.98,0:06:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are these words... a code?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.40,0:06:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do they mean a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.07,0:06:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The doll's name is Mazarin Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.32,0:06:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mazarin Stone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.32,0:06:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Mazarin no Houseki"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.07,0:06:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.91,0:06:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you get the doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.16,0:06:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.16,0:06:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.79,0:06:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beside the bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.37,0:06:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Under the shrubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.04,0:06:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.13,0:06:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can keep it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.25,0:06:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got plenty already!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.26,0:06:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.22,0:07:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.01,0:07:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This might have something to do with that code.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.35,0:07:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.56,0:07:08.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who was distributing the cipher said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If the code doesn't make sense, go to Holmes," didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.11,0:07:15.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, he probably planted items...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.57,0:07:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Related to Holmes in the places indicated by the code, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this "Mazarin Stone" was the title of a\NHolmes story, or so Shinichi told me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.91,0:07:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.33,0:07:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went through all the trouble to make you lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.75,0:07:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you haven't even touched it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.46,0:07:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.80,0:07:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm researching things for a case Inspector\NMegure asked me to look into.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.59,0:07:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.47,0:07:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Burying yourself in deductions to the point\Nwhere you even forget about hunger...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.77,0:07:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll starve to death sooner or later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.27,0:07:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In "The Mazarin Stone," Holmes\Nsaid something similar, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:58.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The faculties become refined when you starve them," it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.57,0:07:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.99,0:08:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I am a brain, Watson."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.49,0:08:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The rest of me is a mere appendix."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.12,0:08:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If everything besides the head is an appendix...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.21,0:08:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means only the head is important!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.63,0:08:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.63,0:08:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.09,0:08:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.97,0:08:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's written here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.70,0:08:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\b0}T!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.06,0:08:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.49,0:08:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.48,0:08:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Certain letters are hidden at the places in the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.73,0:08:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you put them together...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.77,0:08:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll make a word, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.57,0:08:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.73,0:08:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What comes next after "egg" was "pickle," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.28,0:08:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how you think about it, there's no way there\Ncould be a thin disc-shaped building like sliced pickles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.87,0:08:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the code said that he gnawed on a whole pickle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it should be a pickle that hasn't been sliced yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.71,0:08:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.08,0:08:58.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pickles are just pickled young cucumbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.59,0:09:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way such a long, narrow, and\Nround building could exist in this worl—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.14,0:09:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be that, right!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.19,0:09:14.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.31,0:09:16.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks pretty bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.94,0:09:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Hades Sahara guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.61,0:09:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he used to be a hard-working company employee...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.74,0:09:24.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But his mother was struck with a serious disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.74,0:09:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to gather funds for her surgery,\Nhe borrowed from acquaintances...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.08,0:09:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And heavily invested in stocks and with bookies where he lost it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.16,0:09:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that, his mother was unable to receive\Nsurgery and passed away last year in July.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.46,0:09:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The result is that Hades completely changed\Nand started his crime spree.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.59,0:09:46.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He slaughtered not only his acquaintances\Nwho kept hounding him for collection...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.39,0:09:50.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But also his friend who had suggested he invest in stocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.89,0:09:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, he blew up hospitals that had refused\Nto perform his mother's surgery one by one...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.10,0:09:58.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Resulting a large number of casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.23,0:10:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blew up?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.61,0:10:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used explosives too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.32,0:10:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.53,0:10:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While Hades was on the run, he came\Nacross a woman named Hestia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.49,0:10:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's a military outcast and explosives expert.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.74,0:10:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she helped Hades carry out his revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for that woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.37,0:10:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says she blew herself up when the police\Ndiscovered her hideout not too long ago, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the body was blown to bits...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the body could've been someone\Nelse's, and she could still be alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.30,0:10:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.56,0:10:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why hasn't such a dangerous criminal been arrested yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.77,0:10:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he underwent many plastic surgeries while on the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.06,0:10:42.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, with this guy there's no telling what he'll do next.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.48,0:10:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps since this country allows bookies to prey\Non those who bet everything they have...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.49,0:10:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Great Britain itself that he holds a grudge against.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.25,0:10:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.71,0:11:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apologies, but answer it for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.21,0:11:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I answer that phone, it'll be too suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't dawdle, just answer it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.55,0:11:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She may have figured out something about the code!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.14,0:11:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.10,0:11:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hel—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.64,0:11:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,PICK UP THE DAMN PHONE IF YOU'RE THERE, MORON!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.81,0:11:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, that's Ran's phone, right...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.65,0:11:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran was shy and couldn't work up the courage to call you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the great yours truly had to do it himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.57,0:11:33.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this has something to do with Sherlock\NHolmes, you're the number one expert!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.12,0:11:35.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something to do with Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.70,0:11:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.95,0:11:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "egg" in the third line was the egg-shaped City Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.13,0:11:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "pickle" in the fourth line turned out to be the building\Nin the shape of a young cucumber, called the "Gherkin".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.34,0:11:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the problem is that there were Holmes-related\Nitems scattered near those places.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.93,0:11:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of items?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.35,0:11:57.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found dolls near City Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.52,0:12:00.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were words about a Thingamajig Stone on their bod—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.65,0:12:05.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was "Mazarin Stone".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.78,0:12:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said in that story there was a scene where Holmes\Nsaid, "Everything besides the brain is an appendix."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.37,0:12:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.07,0:12:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I pulled off the doll's head, and the letter T appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.91,0:12:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:23.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you use what Holmes says in the story\Nwith the hinted title as a guideline...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.71,0:12:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The keyword to solving the case will be revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.92,0:12:33.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And next to the building called the "Gherkin," a bunch\Nof weird pens with cuts all over had been dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.72,0:12:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Dancing Men" is written on the barrel of the pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.72,0:12:39.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the title of a Holmes story, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.77,0:12:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.89,0:12:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We call it "Odoru Ningyou".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.44,0:12:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I thought something might be in these too...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.73,0:12:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I took off the caps at the tip and the bottom, but still got nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.28,0:12:52.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, try taking the caps from the tip and bottom...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.11,0:12:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And putting them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.03,0:12:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cuts will probably match up at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.54,0:13:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's an N written there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.50,0:13:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.75,0:13:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes said it in that story.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.17,0:13:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If one knocks out all the central inferences and presents one's\Naudience with the starting point and the conclusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"One may produce a startling, though\Npossibly a meretricious, effect."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.52,0:13:20.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:23.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we had to remove the pen's barrel from the middle...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.73,0:13:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And put the caps from the tip and bottom together!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.56,0:13:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, was there anything near Big Ben,\Nwhich is at the beginning of the code?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.15,0:13:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also thought about that and searched for a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.74,0:13:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we couldn't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.28,0:13:43.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad did find a strange arrow drawn on the\Nroad in front of the gate to Big Ben, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.37,0:13:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.54,0:13:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.37,0:13:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a bridge not far from Big Ben, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.29,0:13:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems to be pointing at the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.01,0:13:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.43,0:14:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the bridge, near a drain with\Nits cover removed, there were words written.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.39,0:14:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Valley of Fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.93,0:14:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kyoufu no Tani"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.48,0:14:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.52,0:14:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.81,0:14:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the keyword hidden around here, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.65,0:14:13.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Valley of Fear...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.44,0:14:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a long novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.57,0:14:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there a bridge somewhere in the story?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.45,0:14:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it doesn't have to be a bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.37,0:14:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drain...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.83,0:14:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,River...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.00,0:14:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Water...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.37,0:14:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Water!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.46,0:14:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there something sunk in the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.21,0:14:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"When water is near and a weight is missing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.67,0:14:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It is not a very far-fetched supposition that\Nsomething has been sunk in the water."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.47,0:14:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.47,0:14:43.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there should be something that's\Nbeen sunk into the River Thames.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.19,0:14:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the street lamp attached to the bridge railing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.56,0:14:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a thin rope tied, and the end of\Nthe rope has been sunk in the river!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.15,0:15:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An A!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.91,0:15:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An A has been carved into it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.04,0:15:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The letters that have been found are T, N, and A...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.29,0:15:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.92,0:15:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next place is probably a building that looks like a cake, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.21,0:15:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where should we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.47,0:15:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't get anywhere over the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.51,0:15:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.43,0:15:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be on my way there soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.57,0:15:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine if we just do it over the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.98,0:15:35.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.86,0:15:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've already managed to find three of the keywords ourselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.91,0:15:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that detective brat is here in London...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.78,0:15:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meeting up with him and solving the code\Ntogether would be faster, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or will something inconvenient happen if he comes here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.46,0:15:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.09,0:15:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.55,0:15:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it isn't it the girl from yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.22,0:15:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minerva Glass{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.39,0:16:07.36,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Minerva Glass (22)\NTennis Player
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.42,0:16:01.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Minerva Glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:03.09,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The tennis player?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.49,0:16:05.29,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Is it all right for you to be out and about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.50,0:16:08.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The ladies' singles final is tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.68,0:16:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.60,0:16:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just taking a short break from training.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.31,0:16:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And are you all right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.27,0:16:15.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About your troubles last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.44,0:16:19.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, that person is your boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.65,0:16:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:24.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's troubling me now is a code...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.13,0:16:31.72,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Apollo Glass (22)\NMinerva's Younger Brother
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.23,0:16:26.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A code?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.57,0:16:28.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Then you're just like my little brother Apollo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.47,0:16:31.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It seems ho got a code from a bizarre man...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.46,0:16:34.38,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And gave it to a boy who called himself Holmes's apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.21,0:16:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes's apprentice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.42,0:16:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think his name was Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.47,0:16:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.59,0:16:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said about an Apollo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was actually you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.68,0:16:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know that kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.60,0:16:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.77,0:16:50.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he caught a cold and is sleeping in the hotel today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.52,0:16:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hear that just now, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.56,0:16:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just ran into the boy named Apollo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}\Nwho entrusted Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} with the code...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.11,0:17:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.78,0:17:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An urgent matter came up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.16,0:17:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I can't come and meet you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.45,0:17:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.87,0:17:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.00,0:17:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just got an email saying that a client from\Nanother case is on their way to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.00,0:17:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's an urgent matter, there's no helping it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.05,0:17:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be at the hotel in the meantime, so give me a call anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.01,0:17:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who made the code is a\Nheinous criminal named Hades Sahara.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's not solved soon, things might get really ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.27,0:17:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that Apollo kid is there, have him go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.27,0:17:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he's probably more familiar with London than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.69,0:17:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.32,0:17:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Apollo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.03,0:17:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you come with us and take a stab at the code?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.36,0:17:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.12,0:17:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going back to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.24,0:17:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a massage appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take care of my brother then!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.42,0:17:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.63,0:18:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the next code is "cake," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.96,0:18:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a building like that in London?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.38,0:18:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.72,0:18:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know a place like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:12.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.27,0:18:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really looks like a wedding cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.56,0:18:16.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.60,0:18:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wedding cakes were originally designed\Nto look like the shape of this church.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.15,0:18:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's even named St. Bride's Church...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.40,0:18:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's even named St. Bride's Church...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.28,0:18:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a joke to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.53,0:18:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Apollo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you sure know a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.16,0:18:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I used to come here with my sister all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.29,0:18:35.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She used to say that she and Ares would\Nget married at this church one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.58,0:18:37.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ares?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.21,0:18:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's my sister's former coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.21,0:18:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although my dad used to be Ares's coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.42,0:18:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.72,0:18:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, he passed away in a traffic accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.51,0:18:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.55,0:18:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was while they were on their way to watch Ares's match.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.26,0:18:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That day, my sister caught a cold so she was home with my mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was still in my mom's tummy then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, Ares suddenly said he'd retire from\Nplaying and took over being my sister's coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it seemed that my dad's dream was\Nto train my sister to win at Wimbledon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.66,0:19:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then his dream was fulfilled!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.70,0:19:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.83,0:19:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Ares...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.70,0:19:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He still can't get over the idea that\Nmy dad died because of his match.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.25,0:19:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he broke things off with my sister\Nand even quit being her coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.88,0:19:27.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though he always liked her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.93,0:19:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd say, "In tennis, love is 0...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.26,0:19:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"No matter how many zeroes you add together, you'll just lose."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.97,0:19:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he'd try to act cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.77,0:19:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In tennis, love means zero, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.44,0:19:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.48,0:19:41.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why she said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.90,0:19:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you've also had love troubles?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.19,0:19:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, I'm no longer troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.57,0:19:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how many zeroes you add\Ntogether, you'll just lose miserably.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.08,0:20:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I completely forgot that\NI was supposed to tell her something!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.25,0:20:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell what to who!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.09,0:20:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.09,0:20:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, is it all right if we don't look for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.72,0:20:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be a keyword related to Holmes\Nhidden somewhere around this church, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, we have to search!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.74,0:20:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.86,0:20:33.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You say there are pieces of paper strewn about near\Na church that's shaped like a wedding cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.37,0:20:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what's written on the paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.99,0:20:38.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's written by hand and says...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.45,0:20:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Scandal in Bohemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Bohemia no Shuubun"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.33,0:20:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the story Irene Adler appeared in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.09,0:20:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.92,0:20:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there anything besides the title written on\Nthat paper, or anything strange about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.55,0:20:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The paper is light pink, and the words look\Nlike they were written with a black pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.31,0:21:01.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Other than that, there's nothing strange about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.02,0:21:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The paper is thick and can't be seen through.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.40,0:21:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, but you do not observe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.82,0:21:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm observing it just fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.74,0:21:12.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.95,0:21:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a line that Holmes said to Watson in the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.45,0:21:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a scene where he shows\NWatson a letter with that same color.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.04,0:21:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm to look at the paper more thoroughly,\NI'll have to take it out of its plastic bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.46,0:21:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's inside a plastic bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.42,0:21:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.05,0:21:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, take it out of the bag and soak it in water!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.80,0:21:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The plastic bag is a hint telling us to soak it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.56,0:21:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The water's washing away the letters...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.31,0:21:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S is the only letter that's still distinct!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.23,0:21:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems only the S was written with an oil-based pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.57,0:21:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.69,0:21:53.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The paper was thick in order to hide that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.07,0:21:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were a thin sheet of paper, the letter written with an\Noil-based pen would've bled through to the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.24,0:22:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this means...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.45,0:22:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The keyword from the cake-like St. Bride Church is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.40,0:22:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.63,0:22:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the egg-shaped City Hall, we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.32,0:22:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.34,0:22:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pickle-like building, Gherkin, gave us...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.72,0:22:15.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.13,0:22:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And from Big Ben, the loud sound of a rolling bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.02,0:22:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.31,0:22:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the code, Big Ben appears twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.85,0:22:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if we treat it as if there are two As, we get...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.65,0:22:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,SATAN.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.36,0:22:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.61,0:24:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But a massive murder probably will happen here in London!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.24,0:24:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were at the places shown in the\Ncipher, did you see anyone suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.04,0:24:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I saw a woman wearing sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.09,0:24:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bastard Hades will probably attach\Nbombs to balloons and set them loose, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.63,0:24:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.66,0:24:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.23,0:24:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.91,0:24:50.05,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look Forward to the Next Episode
